    • out

      public static void out(String tag, String message, Object... messageArgs)
      Log a message to the console. Can take a variable number of arguments, which will be formatted into the message. via String.format(). Compatible with format specifiers: %s, %d, %f, %c, %b, %n, %t.

      %s: Used for formatting a string value. %d: Used for formatting an integer value. %f: Used for formatting a floating-point value (decimal number). %c: Used for formatting a character value. %b: Used for formatting a boolean value (true or false). %n: Used for inserting a platform-specific line separator. %t: Used for formatting date and time values.

    • out

      public static void out(boolean conditional, String tag, String message, Object... messageArgs)
      Log based on a boolean conditional. Used for conditional logging in configurations. Well, not used for that directly, but used to make the logs which implement these conditionals, less ugly.
